# Egress proxy allowlist — used by tinyproxy's `Filter` directive.
#
# Format: one regex per line. Tinyproxy matches against the requested
# host. With `FilterDefaultDeny Yes` set, anything not matched is
# blocked, so this file is purely additive.
#
# Operators copy this file to `egress-allowlist.conf` and add the
# domains a given deployment intends to allow `egress-proxied`
# challenges to reach. Restart the egress-proxy service after edits.
#
# Examples (commented out so the default policy is "deny everything"):
# ^api\.example\.com$
# ^.+\.example\.org$
